message: By raking in an annual revenue of $810 million, sex trafficking is one of San Diego's largest underground economies - second only to drug trafficking. San Diego has an important opportunity to be a leader in the fight against human trafficking, especially given our proximity to the U.S. border and the constant movement of people in and out of our area.

data.description: A developing coalition of San Diego-based corporations will focus on preventing the exploitation of human beings as commodities.
data.title: San Diego alliance enlists in fight against human trafficking
